<emphasis id="B916EACBC66DFF9DBA8FFAB5B062FA9C" bold="true" box="[227,348,1381,1407]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C66DFF9DBA8FFA43B44AF9F5" blockId="50.[226,1436,1427,1558]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC66DFF9DBA8FFA43B045FA4E" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1919" box="[227,379,1427,1453]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="50" pageNumber="59" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pelogeniinae">Pelogeniinae</taxonomicName>
with prostomium oval, wider than long. Upper lip without facial tubercle. Median antennal ceratophore bulbous, base without ctenidia. Segment II with or without middorsal triangular lobe; neuropodia with long appendages; neurochaetal blades tapered bifid. Segment III without dorsal cirri; neuropodia without appendages; neurochaetal blades tapered bifurcate. First pair of elytra enlarged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
